=====================
Analysis Work Flow
=====================

.. todo::

    Explain how the analysis is actually orchestrated, in some detail.


When a new analysis is submitted via the user interface, the microservices add this job to a series of queues, so that they are available for consumption. This model is called the Publisher/Subscriber model.

``Archimedes`` uses `Celery <https://www.celeryproject.org>`_ with a `RabbitMQ <https://rabbitmq.com>`_ message queue for the orchestration. ``Celery`` is good at queuing and running tasks, and it works out of the box with ``RabbitMQ``.

In fact, ``Archimedes`` uses message queues for **everything**. The reason for this design is because by adding job runners, it is possible to speed up any operation. The microservice architecture rests upon the shoulders of workers which can be scaled horizontally at any time.

It is paramount that the microservices themselves do not operate on the core tasks themselves, because this way none of them are handling large, time consuming tasks.

Each of the services handles a queue, and the heavy-lifting is carried out by a series of workers.
